<h2>Submit performance metrics</h2>

<p>Performance metrics track how products are performing against key indicators. Submitting metrics regularly ensures accurate operational reporting.</p>

<h3>Accessing the metrics submission page</h3>
<p>Navigate to <strong>Reporting → Operational reporting</strong> from the main navigation menu.</p>

<h3>Understanding reporting requirements</h3>
<p>Before submitting, check if reporting is required for your product:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Products are only shown if reporting is required for the current period</li>
    <li>Business area configurations determine reporting requirements</li>
    <li>Period exclusions may apply</li>
    <li>Check the product list to see which products need metrics</li>
</ul>

<h3>Submitting metrics</h3>
<ol>
    <li>Find your product in the list (or use search/filters)</li>
    <li>Click on the product name</li>
    <li>You'll see the <strong>Submit Metrics</strong> page</li>
    <li>For each metric, enter the required values:
        <ul>
            <li>Some metrics may have default values</li>
            <li>Enter actual values based on your data</li>
            <li>Some fields may be optional</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Review your entries</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong> to save your metrics</li>
</ol>

<h3>Metric types</h3>
<p>Common metric types include:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Usage metrics:</strong> User counts, session data, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance metrics:</strong> Response times, uptime, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Business metrics:</strong> Transactions, conversions, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Quality metrics:</strong> Error rates, satisfaction scores, etc.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Due dates</h3>
<p>Metrics are typically due by the 3rd working day of the following month (configurable by administrators). The system shows:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Current reporting period</li>
    <li>Due date for submission</li>
    <li>Status (upcoming, due, late, or submitted)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Editing submitted metrics</h3>
<p>If you need to correct submitted metrics:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to the product's metrics page</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Edit</strong> on the relevant period</li>
    <li>Update the values</li>
    <li>Save your changes</li>
</ol>
<p>Note: There may be restrictions on editing metrics after the due date.</p>

<h3>Viewing submission history</h3>
<p>To see past submissions:</p>
<ol>
    <li>Go to your product's page</li>
    <li>Click <strong>View History</strong></li>
    <li>See all previous submissions with dates and values</li>
</ol>

<h3>Best practices</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Submit metrics on time to avoid late status</li>
    <li>Double-check values before submitting</li>
    <li>Use consistent data sources</li>
    <li>Document any anomalies or unusual values</li>
    <li>Keep historical data for comparison</li>
    <li>Contact administrators if you have questions about specific metrics</li>
</ul>

<h3>Getting help</h3>
<p>If you need assistance:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Check the metric definitions and guidance</li>
    <li>Contact your business area administrator</li>
    <li>Review the product history to see previous submissions</li>
    <li>Check if your product is excluded from reporting for this period</li>
</ul>

